descriptionHtml:
Been playing as this character for a bit, figured I'd share.

REQUIRED REGARDLESS OF WHAT YOU DO: [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/29624/?]Racemenu + it's requirements.[/url]

She's a Breton, she likes magic. There are two files, one which has a back tattoo and uses a different eye texture.

For the bretonmagegirl.jslot (this file just uses vanilla eyes) to get her to look like she does in my screenshot you will need:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/52841/?]This mod for the freckles[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/60243/]This mod for the facial makeup/warpaint
[/url][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/35327/?]This mod for the eyebrows
[/url][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/10168/?]This mod for the hair[/url][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/29624/?]
[/url][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/33117/?]This for the teeth
[/url][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/32986/?]This for the body
[/url]
For the bretonmagegirlabereyes.jslot you will need everything listed above plus:
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/59192/?]This mod for the eyes
[/url][url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/50032/?]This mod for the dragon tattoo on her back
[/url]

Installation:
Just open the zip, should see a data folder inside. Open it, drag the SKSE folder into your data folder where you have skyrim installed to. Open up the "showracemenu" command in the game and go to the presets tab, load either preset you like. Done!

Credits:
I made this but whatever. It's not like I can claim copyrights or anything. If you want to change her, please by all means do. I just uploaded her because I liked her. If you want to post screens of her in your game, please do as well!
